%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20US%20military%20is%20exploring%20blood%20biohacks%20to%20boost%20warfighter%20performance%20in%20extreme%20conditions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222700%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Coalition%20special%20operations%20forces%20members%20sprint%20to%20board%20a%20UH-60%20Black%20Hawk%20helicopter%20during%20a%20mission%20in%20Kunar%20province%2C%20Afghanistan%2C%20Feb.%2025.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67901fe72fcded5e90742257%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECoalition%20special%20operations%20forces%20members%20sprint%20to%20board%20a%20UH-60%20Black%20Hawk%20helicopter%20during%20a%20mission%20in%20Kunar%20province%2C%20Afghanistan.%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Navy%20photo%20by%20Mass%20Communication%20Specialist%202nd%20Class%20Clay%20Weis%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDARPA%20seeks%20to%20modify%20red%20blood%20cells%20to%20enhance%20troop%20performance.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Red%20Blood%20Cell%20Factory%20program%20aims%20to%20insert%20biologically%20active%20components%20in%20cells.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20agency%20says%20this%20research%20could%20one%20day%20lead%20to%20longer-lasting%20meds%20and%20blood-cell%20drug%20delivery%20systems.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Defense%20Advanced%20Research%20Project%20Agency%2C%20the%20Pentagon's%20top%20research%20arm%2C%20wants%20to%20know%20if%20red%20blood%20cells%20can%20be%20modified%20in%20novel%20ways%20to%20protect%20troops%20and%20help%20them%20manage%20extreme%20battlefield%20environments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DARPA%20program%2C%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BRed%20Blood%20Cell%20Factory%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20looking%20for%20researchers%20and%20is%20interested%20in%20inserting%20%26quot%3Bbiologically%20active%20components%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bcargoes%26quot%3B%20in%20red%20blood%20cells.%20The%20hope%20is%20that%20modified%20cells%20would%20bring%20with%20them%20special%20enhancements%2C%20%26quot%3Bthus%20allowing%20recipients%2C%20such%20as%20warfighters%2C%20to%20operate%20more%20effectively%20in%20dangerous%20or%20extreme%20environments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERed%20blood%20cells%20could%20act%20like%20a%20truck%2C%20carrying%20%26quot%3Bcargo%26quot%3B%20or%20special%20protections%2C%20to%20all%20parts%20of%20the%20body%2C%20since%20they%20already%20circulate%20oxygen%20everywhere%2C%20Christopher%20Bettinger%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20biomedical%20engineering%20overseeing%20the%20program%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20if%20we%20could%20add%20in%20additional%20cargo%20%E2%80%A6%20inside%20of%20that%20disc%2C%26quot%3B%20Bettinger%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20shape%20of%20red%20blood%20cells%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20could%20then%20confer%20these%20interesting%20benefits%20%E2%80%A6%20protective%20capabilities%20that%20we're%20trying%20to%20sort%20of%20imbue%20to%20our%20warfighters%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20soldiers%20on%20patrol%20in%20forest%20area%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679025b9ae09223df2bae8ed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221391%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20soldiers%20on%20patrol%20a%20mountain%20pass%20of%20Kunar%20province%2C%20Afghanistan's%20Korengal%20Valley%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Army%20Sgt.%20Matthew%20Moeller%2C%205th%20Mobile%20Public%20Affairs%20Detachment%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c93ced80-a638-4892-9ca8-49679ef055b7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20could%20these%20modifications%20do%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDARPA%20does%20not%20expect%20the%20researchers%20to%20experiment%20on%20people%20or%20animals%2C%20just%20on%20bags%20of%20blood.%20The%20research%20is%20foundational%2C%20Bettinger%20said%2C%20but%20could%20allow%20scientists%20to%20identify%20how%20red%20blood%20cell%20modification%20could%20evolve%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20could%20impact%20the%20way%20troops%20battle%20diseases%20that%20reproduce%20in%20red%20blood%20cells%20such%20as%20malaria%2C%20for%20example%2C%20Bettinger%20hypothesized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BImagine%20an%20alternative%20world%20where%20we%20have%20a%20warfighter%20that%20has%20a%20red%20blood%20cell%20that's%20accessorized%20with%20a%20compound%20that%20can%20sort%20of%20defeat%20malaria%2C%26quot%3B%20Bettinger%20said.%20In%20this%20scenario%2C%20a%20red%20blood%20cell%20could%20be%20%26quot%3Baccessorized%26quot%3B%20with%20a%20countermeasure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20kind%20of%20like%20an%20automatic%20drug%20delivery%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20could%20then%20protect%20the%20warfighter%20from%20the%20harmful%20effects%20of%20subsequent%20infection%20and%20sort%20of%20replication%20of%20the%20parasite.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20also%20be%20possible%20to%20modify%20the%20red%20blood%20cells%20in%20ways%20that%20would%20allow%20medications%20to%20last%20longer%20without%20a%20service%20member%20having%20to%20ingest%20them%20daily%20%E2%80%94%20instead%2C%20relying%20on%20doses%20that%20protect%20a%20person%20for%20weeks%20or%20months%20instead%20of%20just%2024%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20potential%20use%20of%20modified%20cells%20could%20be%20stopping%20a%20hemorrhage%20from%20trauma%2C%20including%20battlefield%20wounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTrauma%20induces%20a%20kind%20of%20host%20of%20biological%20responses%2C%20one%20of%20which%20is%20rupturing%20of%20red%20blood%20cells%2C%26quot%3B%20Bettinger%20said.%20DARPA's%20research%20efforts%20could%20ascertain%20from%20its%20blood%20research%20whether%20a%20catastrophic%20injury%20that%20would%20normally%20mean%20death%20from%20blood%20loss%20instead%20sees%20blood%20automatically%20coagulate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225616%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Five%20US%20Marines%20patrolling%20a%20desert%20area%20in%20Afghanistan.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6790263e10c98eace9135465%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223744%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Marines%20conduct%20a%20patrol%20out%20of%20Forward%20Operating%20Base%20Tabac%20in%20Sangin%2C%20Helmand%20province%2C%20Afghanistan%3Cp%3EMarine%20Corps%20photo%20by%20Pfc.%20Jason%20Morrison%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222413a276-0564-4228-839e-3c0b5556a1fc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20path%20to%20a%20more%20capable%20warfighter%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEach%20red%20blood%20cell%20stays%20in%20the%20blood%20for%20about%20four%20months%2C%20and%20it%20accesses%20pretty%20much%20every%20organ%20in%20the%20body%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Samir%20Mitragotri%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mitragotrilab.seas.harvard.edu%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebioengineering%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Harvard.%20Their%20prevalence%20and%20relatively%20long%20lifetime%20are%20partly%20why%20red%20blood%20cells%20are%20such%20an%20attractive%20target%20for%20scientists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20challenge%2C%20Mitragotri%20said%2C%20is%20that%20the%20cells%20can't%20be%20so%20radically%20changed%20that%20the%20body%20no%20longer%20recognizes%20them%20as%20red%20blood%20cells%2C%20thus%20prompting%20quicker%20bodily%20digestion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20advances%20in%20bioengineering%20could%20be%20a%20game-changer%20in%20fields%20like%20infectious%20disease%20treatment%20and%20oncology%2C%20said%20Mitragotri%2C%20illnesses%20which%20require%20long%20periods%20of%20drug%20treatment.%20Though%20the%20science%20is%20still%20emerging%2C%20it's%20%26quot%3Ba%20very%20promising%20area%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Defense%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F3-strangest-projects-from-darpa-mind-control-force-field-parapsychology-2017-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elong%20been%20interested%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20learning%20how%20biomedical%20engineering%20could%20benefit%20troops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20the%20US%20military%20has%20been%20looking%20into%20the%20benefits%20of%20biofeedback%20technologies%20to%20better%20understand%20mental%20and%20physical%20health.%20And%20there's%20also%20been%20research%20into%20potential%20physical%20enhancements%20through%20various%20lines%20of%20effort.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20Army%20released%20a%20%26quot%3BCyborg%20Soldier%202050%26quot%3B%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheres-what-worries-the-military-about-future-cyborg-super-soldiers-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edetailing%3C%2Fa%3E%20how%20the%20military%20is%20thinking%20about%20a%20future%20where%20troops%20could%20benefit%20from%20things%20like%20neural%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F15-current-darpa-innovations-2014-7%23a-system-that-gives-soldiers-enhanced-optical-awareness-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoptical%3C%2Fa%3E%20enhancements%2C%20though%20the%20report%20acknowledged%20ethical%20and%20legal%20concerns%20surrounding%20such%20possibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20rivals%20like%20China%20are%2C%20as%20the%20Foundation%20for%20the%20Defense%20of%20Democracies%20noted%20in%20a%20new%20report%2C%20also%20exploring%20this%20space%2C%20but%20with%20less%20concern%20for%20ethical%20considerations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20People's%20Liberation%20Army%20%26quot%3Bhas%20long%20recognized%20the%20strategic%20importance%20of%20biotechnology%2C%20engaging%20in%20extensive%20collaborations%20with%20Chinese%20biotechnology%20behemoths%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20and%20other%20partnerships%20have%20yielded%20research%20with%20potential%20military%20applications%2C%20including%20efforts%20to%20enhance%20Chinese%20soldiers'%20physical%20and%20cognitive%20abilities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdarpa-exploring-how-blood-biohacks-could-help-warfighters-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737541802000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6790263e10c98eace9135465%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdarpa-exploring-how-blood-biohacks-could-help-warfighters-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22DARPA%20wants%20to%20know%20if%20modifying%20red%20blood%20cells%20can%20help%20warfighters%20%26quot%3Boperate%20more%20effectively%20in%20dangerous%20or%20extreme%20environments.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kbaker%40businessinsider.com%20(Kelsey%20Baker)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdarpa-exploring-how-blood-biohacks-could-help-warfighters-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22MVP%20Kids%20Scores%20Toonz%20Media%2C%20BLKBX%20Originals%20Deal%20for%20TV%20Series%2C%20Roblox%20Game%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737541449000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F01%2FMVP-Kids.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236281731%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India-headquartered%20global%20animation%20outfit%20Toonz%20Media%20Group%20is%20betting%20big%20on%20character-building%20entertainment%2C%20partnering%20with%20BLKBX%20Originals%20and%20MVP%20Kids%20to%20develop%20a%20new%203D%20animated%20series%20and%20Roblox%20game%20based%20on%20the%20popular%20children%E2%80%99s%20brand.%20The%20deal%20will%20see%20the%20production%20of%2052%20seven-minute%20episodes%20aimed%20at%20expanding%20the%20reach%20of%20MVP%20Kids%E2%80%99%20diverse%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Naman%20Ram