uot%3BWhat%20are%20the%20top%20things%20that%20really%20showcase%20the%20impact%20that%20you've%20made%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEscalera%20said%20it%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20an%20exhaustive%20list.%20She%20added%20that%20if%20there%20are%20smaller%20accomplishments%20that%20don't%20warrant%20being%20mentioned%20in%20a%20discussion%20over%20compensation%2C%20they%20could%20serve%20as%20the%20basis%20for%20asking%20a%20client%20or%20a%20colleague%20for%20a%20LinkedIn%20endorsement%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeeping%20a%20list%20can%20also%20help%20identify%20when%20it%20might%20be%20time%20to%20ask%20for%20an%20increase%20in%20compensation%20or%20a%20heftier%20title%2C%20even%20outside%20an%20annual%20review%20cycle%2C%20Escalera%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToo%20often%2C%20she%20said%2C%20workers%20shy%20away%20from%20discussing%20their%20achievements%20because%20they%20want%20to%20avoid%20the%20appearance%20of%20bragging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20stop%20ourselves%20from%20self-promotion%20because%20we%20think%20it's%20bad%2C%20but%20self-promotion%20is%20the%20breadcrumbs%20that%20lead%20to%20the%20titles%20and%20the%20promotions%20and%20the%20pay%20raises%2C%26quot%3B%20Escalera%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2205a855ed-1f09-41ce-ab88-63fdac7dd936%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EKnow%20your%20financial%20worth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20way%20to%20feel%20less%20uneasy%20about%20promoting%20ourselves%20is%20to%20have%20a%20sense%20of%20what%20others%20in%20similar%20roles%20at%20other%20organizations%20are%20earning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20that%20data%20on%20hand%20can%20appeal%20to%20many%20bosses'%20desire%20to%20be%20competitive%20in%20the%20marketplace%20and%20even%20to%20live%20up%20to%20the%20values%20the%20organization%20espouses%2C%20Maria%20Ross%2C%20who%20researches%20empathy%20and%20is%20the%20author%20of%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BThe%20Empathy%20Dilemma%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20workers%20who%20have%20information%20about%20pay%20rates%20at%20other%20organizations%20and%20who%20have%20deep%20knowledge%20about%20the%20state%20of%20their%20employer's%20business%20are%20likely%20to%20fare%20better%20in%20a%20discussion%20about%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoss%20suggested%20people%20should%20consider%20how%20getting%20a%20raise%20might%20benefit%20the%20organization.%20A%20hike%20in%20pay%20might%20come%20with%20added%20responsibility%20or%20taking%20on%20some%20of%20your%20boss's%20work.%20Or%2C%20she%20said%2C%20if%20you%20get%20a%20promotion%2C%20that%20could%20create%20an%20opening%20for%20someone%20to%20move%20into%20your%20old%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20can%20you%20frame%20the%20ask%20as%20a%20benefit%20to%20the%20organization%3F%26quot%3B%20Ross%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22912adf20-9bb0-4d51-995d-6056287e5936%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20make%20it%20an%20easy%20'no'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOften%2C%20workers%20consider%20themselves%20lucky%20to%20have%20a%20job.%20While%20that%20might%20be%20true%2C%20the%20organization%20can%20also%20be%20lucky%20to%20have%20you%2C%20Julie%20Smith%2C%20author%20of%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BCoach%20Yourself%20Confident%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20kind%20of%20a%20scary%20thing%20to%20ask%2C%20'Do%20you%20think%20I'm%20worth%20more%3F'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20said%20the%20discussion%20over%20a%20bump%20in%20pay%20might%20end%20up%20spilling%20into%20more%20than%20one%20conversation%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that's%20OK.%20That's%20because%2C%20sometimes%2C%20raising%20the%20topic%20of%20a%20pay%20increase%20can%20prompt%20a%20busy%20boss%20to%20pay%20more%20attention%20to%20all%20of%20the%20things%20you're%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20instead%20of%20asking%20for%20a%20raise%20immediately%2C%20you%20might%20benefit%20from%20asking%20your%20boss%20to%20consider%20a%20pay%20bump%2C%20or%20that%20your%20boss%20brings%2