mmends%20an%20%3Cem%3Eelevated%3C%2Fem%3E%20version%20of%20the%20stretch%2C%20which%20is%20easier%20on%20the%20knee%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERest%20one%20knee%20on%20a%20bench%20or%20box%20near%20the%20wall.%20Bend%20that%20knee%20while%20moving%20the%20shin%20and%20top%20of%20the%20foot%20to%20rest%20flat%20up%20against%20the%20wall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20it's%20painful%2C%20ease%20up%20on%20the%20stretch%2C%20especially%20if%20you%20have%20an%20injury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimeonovski%20said%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-avoid-common-gym-injuries-physical-therapist-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20way%20to%20avoid%20injury%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20pay%20attention%20%E2%80%94%20if%20something%20is%20painful%20enough%20that%20it's%20distracting%2C%20or%20if%20you%20stop%20the%20exercise%20and%20the%20pain%20persists%2C%20don't%20continue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPain%20that%20lingers%20is%20a%20red%20flag%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22806331cf-285d-484c-a2d4-ca113b54e813%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHamstring%20curls%20can%20protect%20your%20knees%20from%20injury%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESimeonovski%20said%20the%20hamstrings%2C%20the%20muscles%20on%20the%20back%20of%20the%20leg%2C%20are%20often%20overlooked.%20We%20tend%20to%20focus%20on%20the%20quads%20on%20the%20front%20of%20the%20leg.%20But%20that%20can%20increase%20the%20risk%20of%20damaging%20ligaments%20in%20the%20knee%20because%20the%20quads%20can%20put%20too%20much%20pressure%20on%20the%20ACL%20without%20the%20hamstrings%20to%20counteract%20them.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20strengthen%20the%20hamstrings%2C%20try%20Nordic%20hamstring%20curls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStart%20in%20a%20kneeling%20position%20with%20your%20feet%20secured%20(you%20can%20use%20a%20special%20mat%20or%20bench%2C%20tuck%20them%20under%20a%20couch%20or%20other%20furniture%2C%20or%20have%20someone%20hold%20them).%20Keeping%20your%20torso%2C%20hips%2C%20and%20shoulders%20in%20a%20straight%20line%2C%20slowly%20lower%20yourself%20to%20the%20ground%2C%20landing%20on%20your%20hands%20as%20if%20in%20the%20bottom%20of%20push-up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20exercise%20can%20be%20challenging.%20If%20you%20feel%20like%20you%20don't%20have%20control%2C%20use%20a%20resistance%20band%20secured%20behind%20you%20to%20help%20offset%20some%20of%20your%20body%20weight.%20That%20will%20make%20the%20movement%20easier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fc1a025d-16d8-4692-bc21-d047d2275926%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EStep-ups%20strengthen%20the%20knee%20and%20help%20fix%20imbalances%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20doing%20a%20step-up%20exercise%20at%20the%20gym%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6786d3bd50dfd88e193e68ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStep-ups%20can%20help%20address%20muscle%20imbalances%20by%20focusing%20on%20one%20leg%20at%20a%20time%2C%20while%20also%20improving%20lower%20body%20strength%20and%20stability.%3Cp%3EZinkevych%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Simeonovski's%20go-to%20exercises%20for%20improving%20lower%20body%20strength%20and%20joint%20health%20is%20the%20step-up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStand%20in%20front%20of%20a%20stool%2C%20bench%2C%20box%2C%20or%20stairs%2C%20and%20place%20one%20foot%20on%20the%20elevated%20surface.%20Pressing%20through%20that%20foot%2C%20lift%20your%20body%20up%20onto%20the%20step%2C%20and%20then%20return%20to%20the%20starting%20position.%20Repeat%2C%20alternating%20the%20starting%20foot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStep-ups%20are%20low-impact%20and%20work%20the%20glutes%2C%20hamstrings%2C%20and%20quads%20as%20well%20as%20the%20core%20muscles.%20Alternating%20sides%20can%20also%20help%20improve%20your%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGo%20slow%20and%20gradually%20increase%20weight%2C%20height%2C%20or%20intensity%20as%20you%20get%20comfortable%20with%20the%20exercise.%20Squats%20and%20lunges%20offer%20similar%20benefits%2C%20but%20may%20need%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsquat-knees-over-toes-is-it-bad-myth-trainer-advice-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emodifications%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20you%20have%20an%20existing%20injury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimeonovski%20said%20he%20prefers%20these%20movements%20to%20exercises%20like%20knee%20extensions%2C%20which%20aren't%20necessarily%20bad%20for%20your%20joints%2C%20but%20don't%20offer%20as%20much%20stability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220ee6d4fa-3ef8-4311-a58c-8f86c85b9e39%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERotational%20exercise%20helps%20to%20offset%20damage%20from%20sitting%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20athlete%20in%20leggings%20and%20a%20sports%20bra%20performing%20a%20side%20lying%20twist%20stretch%20on%20a%20mat%20in%20a%20living%20room%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6786ae628951662c9f202377%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20open%20book%3A%20Stretching%20your%20spine%20can%20help%20improve%20overall%20movement%20and%20prevent%20back%20and%20hip%20pain.%3Cp%3ESimpleImages%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETightness%20in%20one%20area%20can%20cause%20a%20chain%20reaction%20and%20create%20aches%20and%20issues%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20back%20problems%20can%20worsen%20strain%20and%20pressure%20on%20the%20knees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20Simeonovski%20recommends%20the%20open%20book%20exercise%20for%20patients%20who%20have%20knee%20pain%20and%20spend%20lots%20of%20time%20sitting.%20It%20doesn't%20directly%20involve%20the%20knees%20but%20can%20improve%20overall%20mobility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELie%20on%20a%20mat%20or%20the%20floor%20with%20your%20knees%20and%20hips%20bent%20at%2090%20degrees%20and%20your%20arms%20extended%20in%20front%20of%20you.%20Slowly%20rotate%20the%20top%20arm%20up%20and%20across%20your%20body%20as%20far%20as%20you%20comfortably%20can%2C%20gently%20twisting%20your%20spine.%20Return%20to%20the%20starting%20position%20and%20repeat%2C%20being%20sure%20to%20perform%20the%20exercise%20on%20both%20sides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20also%20do%20a%20similar%20rotation%20from%20a%20half-kneeling%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b8bccd6e-9c90-4276-b335-bb3533860dd4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETake%20breaks%20for%20movement%20throughout%20the%20day%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20to%20strengthening%20and%20protecting%20your%20joints%20is%20consistency%2C%20especially%20if%20you%20sit%20all%20day%2C%20according%20to%20Simeonovski.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFind%20opportunities%20to%20get%20up%20and%20move%20around%20at%20regular%20intervals%2C%20setting%20an%20alarm%20if%20needed%20to%20remind%20yourself%20to%20take%20a%20stretch%20break%2C%20go%20for%20a%20short%20walk%2C%20or%20otherwise%20give%20your%20body%20a%20rest%20from%20repetition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStaying%20in%20one%20position%20is%20a%20problem%20long-term%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffix-knee-pain-and-prevent-injury-exercises-physical-therapist-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737538262000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6786b043e294a7514e8d1086%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffix-knee-pain-and-prevent-injury-exercises-physical-therapist-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20physical%20therapist%20said%20that%20sitting%20all%20day%20can%20cause%20knee%20pain%2C%20but%20simple%20exercises%20can%20help%20strengthen%20and%20stabilize%20the%20joints.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22glandsverk%40insider.com%20(Gabby%20Landsverk)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2