%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegeneration.VC%20will%20still%20be%20investing%20in%20the%20US%20because%20of%20its%20%26quot%3Bgreat%20pools%20of%20capital%20and%20risk%20appetite%2C%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20but%20Rowles%20emphasized%20that%20being%20aligned%20with%20the%20European%20Union%20on%20climate%20was%20a%20huge%20priority%20for%20the%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20see%20more%20climate%20tech%20funds%20with%20more%20of%20a%20presence%20in%20Europe%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20reality%20is%2C%20you%20need%20to%20be%20in%20both%20markets%20to%20do%20the%20type%20of%20work%20we're%20doing.%20But%20in%20Europe%2C%20there's%20better%20regulation%20and%20better%20mechanisms%20to%20avoid%20greenwashing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fregeneration-vc-sky-climate-portfolio-europe-partner-leonardo-di-caprio-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737536401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678fcd1e2fcded5e9073fbe7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fregeneration-vc-sky-climate-portfolio-europe-partner-leonardo-di-caprio-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Climate%20tech%20fund%20Regeneration.VC%2C%20backed%20by%20Leonardo%20DiCaprio%2C%20is%20doubling%20down%20in%20Europe%20as%20the%20continent%20attracts%20more%20climate%20tech%20funds.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22rkanetkar%40insider.com%20(Riddhi%20Kanetkar)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fregeneration-vc-sky-climate-portfolio-europe-partner-leonardo-di-caprio-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20How%20China%20Quietly%20Made%20New%20Friends%20To%20Prepare%20For%20Trump%202.0%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDonald%20Trump's%20declaration%20in%20his%20inaugural%20address%20on%20Monday%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20golden%20age%20of%20America%20begins%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20may%20align%20with%20his%20electoral%20promise%20to%20Make%20America%20Great%20Again%20(MAGA).%20Perhaps%20it%20signals%20an%20extension%20of%20his%20MAGA%20slogan.%20Where%20MAGA%20focuses%20on%20reclaiming%20a%20perceived%20lost%20greatness%20through%20economic%20nationalism%2C%20deregulation%2C%20and%20%26quot%3BAmerica%20First%26quot%3B%20foreign%20policy%2C%20the%20%26quot%3BGolden%20Age%26quot%3B%2C%20though%20boastful%2C%20could%20mean%20a%20forward-looking%20promise%20of%20prosperity%20and%20strength.%20It%20implies%20a%20renewed%20sense%20of%20optimism%20but%20also%20carries%20the%20weight%20of%20delivering%20tangible%20results%20in%20a%20deeply%20polarised%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20China%20Is%20Important%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20also%20pledged%20to%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bpeacemaker%20and%20unifier%26quot%3B%2C%20which%20sat%20well%20with%20his%20anti-war%20stance.%20But%20to%20make%20America%20great%20again%20or%20birth%20the%20%26quot%3Bgolden%20age%20of%20America%26quot%3B%2C%20Trump%20will%20need%20more%20than%20mere%20slogans.%20Common%20wisdom%20says%20that%20he'll%20need%20to%20focus%20on%20economic%20recovery%2C%20geopolitical%20stability%20and%20ever-deepening%20domestic%20division%20to%20achieve%20his%20goal.%20But%20there's%20one%20area%20most%20important%20of%20all%3A%20managing%20US-China%20ties%2C%20the%20most%20critical%20bilateral%20relations%20in%20the%20world%20right%20now.%20The%20geopolitical%20reality%20is%20that%20there%20is%20no%20other%20country%20that%20threatens%20the%20US%20global%20hegemony%20more%20than%20China%2C%20now%20and%20more%20so%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20Trump's%20victory%2C%20there%20have%20been%20reams%20of%20analyses%20in%20Western%20media%20and%20think%20tank%20circles%2C%20many%20of%20which%20predict%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20second%20Cold%20War%20or%20the%20demise%20of%20the%20Chinese%20economy.%20Yet%2C%20the%20fact%20is%20that%20while%20Trump%20in%20his%20election%20campaign%20had%20resolved%20to%20slap%20a%2060%25%20tariff%20on%20all%20Chinese%20imports%2C%20following%20his%20inauguration%2C%20he%20said%20he%20is%20considering%20a%2010%25%20tariff%20instead%20on%20imports%20of%20Chinese-made%20goods.%20This%20may%20come%20into%20effect%20as%20soon%20as%20February%201.%20So%2C%20while%20the%20West%20unnecessarily%20and%20endlessly%20replay%20Donald%20Trump's%20first-term%20rhetoric%20to%20paint%20him%20as%20China's%20eternal%20nemesis%2C%20the%20reality%20this%20time%20may%20be%20different.%20Let's%20not%20overlook%20Trump's%20positive%20gestures%20towards%20China%20and%20its%20president%20in%20recent%20days.%20He%20went%20out%20of%20his%20way%20to%20invite%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20as%20a%20special%20guest%20to%20his%20inauguration%2C%20and%2C%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20this%20spectacle%2C%20the%20two%20leaders%20even%20had%20a%20phone%20call.%20That%20couldn't%20have%20been%20to%20discuss%20the%20weather%2C%20surely.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20suggests%20that%20the%20two%20leaders%20can%20still%20talk%20shop.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump%20Chooses%20Balance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20US%20President%20also%20came%20out%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Chinese-owned%20app%20TikTok%2C%20pledging%20to%20delay%20the%20enforcement%20of%20a%20US%20ban%3B%20he%20has%20even%20promised%20to%20find%20an%20American%20buyer%2C%20suggesting%20a%2050%25%20buyout.%20This%20comes%20nearly%20five%20years%20after%20Trump%20tried%20to%20ban%20the%20short-video-sharing%20platform%20himself.%20It%20went%20dark%20in%20the%20US%20for%20a%20bit%20this%20weekend%20but%20was%20reinstated%20after%20Trump's%20reassurances.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20signing%20executive%20orders%20on%20his%20first%20day%20in%20office%2C%20Trump%20shared%20his%20satisfaction%20with%20his%20recent%20phone%20call%20with%20Xi%2C%20saying%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bvery%20good%26quot%3B.%20And%20though%20Xi%20did%20not%20attend%20the%20inauguration%20himself%2C%20he%20dispatched%20Vice-President%20Han%20Zheng%20to%20take%20part%20in%20the%20swearing-in%20festivities.%20Han%20seemed%20to%20have%20a%20more%20productive%20time%20in%20Washington%20than%20most%20pundits%20anticipated.%20He%20didn't%20waste%20a%20moment%2C%20meeting%20Tesla's%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20who%20reiterated%20his%20commitment%20to%20investing%20more%20in%20China.%20The%20Chinese%20Vice-President%20also%20sat%20down%20with%20a%20group%20of%20American%20business%20leaders%2C%20giving%20them%20the%20classic%20Chinese%20pitch%3A%20keep%20those%20investments%20flowing%2C%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20promised%20to%20declare%20on%20the%20very%20first%20day%20in%20the%20White%20House%20a%2010%25%20tariff%20on%20imports%20from%20all%20countries%2C%2025%25%20on%20goods%20from%20Canada%20and%20Mexico%2C%20and%2060%25%20on%20Chinese%20imports.%20In%20his%20inaugural%20speech%2C%20however%2C%20these%20things%20were%20mentioned%20only%20in%20generic%20terms.%20No%20doubt%20Trump's%20return%20has%20created%20a%20sense%20of%20uncertainty%2C%20but%20does%20it%20make%20sense%20to%20obsess%20over%20tariffs%2C%20especially%20with%20regard%20to%20China%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho's%20The%20Real%20Nemesis%2C%20Biden%20or%20Trump%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EContrary%20to%20popular%20notion%20that%20Trump%20was%20the%20ultimate%20China%20hawk%20%E2%80%94what%20with%20his%20administration%20slapping%20tariffs%20on%20over%20%24360%20billion%20worth%20of%20Chinese%20goods%2C%20blacklisting%20tech%20firms%20like%20Huawei%2C%20and%20issuing%20at%20least%20eight%20executive%20orders%20directly%20targeting%20the%20country%E2%80%94the%20reality%20is%20that%20Joe%20Biden%20had%20been%20much%20tougher.%20While%20Trump's%20approach%20was%20often%20loud%20and%20unilateral%2C%20Biden's%20strategy%20was%20quieter%20but%20far%20more%20expansive%20and%20coordinated%2C%20signalling%20a%20long-term%20containment%20plan%20rather%20than%20a%20short-term%20trade%20skirmish.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20didn't%20just%20inherit%20Trump-era%20tariffs%2C%20he%20doubled%20down%20on%20them.%20Not%20only%20did%20he%20keep%20most%20of%20Trump's%20tariffs%20intact%20but%20he%20also%20expanded%20the%20list%20of%20goods%20subject%20to%20higher%20duties.%20Last%20year%2C%20he%20imposed%20a%20100%25%20tariff%20on%20Chinese%20green%20buses%20and%20electric%20vehicles%2C%20a%20move%20aimed%20squarely%20at%20countering%20China's%20push%20for%20global%20dominance%20in%20the%20renewable%20energy%20sector.%20Additionally%2C%20he%20tightened%20export%20controls%20on%20semiconductors%20and%20chip-making%20technologies%2C%20effectively%20cutting%20China%20off%20from%20critical%20components%20required%20for%20its%20tech%20sector.%20This%20was%20coupled%20with%20sanctions%20targeting%20firms%20tied%20to%20Chinese%20military%20advancements%2C%20particularly%20in%20AI%20and%20quantum%20computing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBiden%20Went%20All%20Out%20On%20China%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20went%20global%20with%20his%20anti-China%20strategy.%20He%20rallied%20friends%20and%20partners%20to%20join%20in%20pressuring%20Beijing.%20Under%20his%20administration%2C%20the%20US%20strengthened%20the%20QUAD%20(a%20strategic%20grouping%20of%20the%20US%2C%20Japan%2C%20India%20and%20Australia)%20and%20expanded%20its%20focus%20to%20counter%20China's%20growing%20influence%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific.%20Biden%20also%20courted%20India%20with%20unprecedented%20vigour%2C%20offering%20military%20deals%2C%20economic%20partnerships%20and%20support%20in%20global%20fora%20to%20pull%20New%20Delhi%20further%20into%20Washington's%20orbit.%20He%20also%20gave%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20a%20state%20visit%2C%20a%20rarity%20in%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20wasn't%20all.%20Biden%20strengthened%20NATO's%20focus%20on%20China%2C%20a%20significant%20shift%20for%20a%20transatlantic%20alliance%20originally%20centred%20on%20Russia.%20Under%20his%20leadership%2C%20NATO%20for%20the%20first%20time%20identified%20China%20as%20a%20systemic%20challenge%20in%20its%20official%20documents%2C%20signalling%20a%20broader%20geopolitical%20pivot.%20Also%2C%20Biden%20built%20a%20coalition%20of%20nations%20to%20exclude%20Chinese%20tech%20giants%20like%20Huawei%20and%20ZTE%20from%20critical%20infrastructure%20projects%2C%20particularly%20in%205G%20networks.%20On%20the%20economic%20front%2C%20his%20administration%20launched%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20Economic%20Framework%20(IPEF)%2C%20aimed%20at%20offering%20an%20alternative%20to%20China's%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiative.%20By%20working%20closely%20with%20ASEAN%20countries%2C%20South%20Korea%20and%20Japan%2C%20Biden%20tried%20to%20reduce%20regional%20dependency%20on%20Chinese%20trade%20and%20investment%20while%20simultaneously%20boosting%20American%20influence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrade%20War%20Or%20Trade%20Tango%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20the%20anticipation%20in%20the%20West%20of%20a%20second%20%E2%80%98Cold%20War'%20under%20Trump%20holds%20some%20merit%2C%20it's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20a%20one-sided%20affair.%20Let's%20not%20forget%20that%20Beijing%20has%20been%20busy%20laying%20the%20groundwork%20to%20ensure%20that%20American%20companies%20remain%20tethered%20to%20China's%20vast%20market.%20This%20time%2C%20it%20appears%20China%20is%20ready%20for%20whatever%20the%20US%20throws%20at%20it%2C%20a%20trade%20game%20or%20a%20trade%20tango.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20preparation%20for%20any%20potential%20economic%20storm%20triggered%20by%20Trump's%20tariffs%2C%20China%20has%20been%20quietly%20and%20strategically%20diversifying%20its%20trade%20and%20investment%20networks.%20Their%20efforts%20span%20continents%2C%20trade%20blocs%20and%20key%20partnerships%2C%20creating%20a%20robust%20web%20of%20economic%20connections%20that%20might%20just%20blunt%20any%20future%20US%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFriends%20In%20Various%20Places%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsider%20China's%20deepening%20relationship%20with%20ASEAN.%20As%20one%20of%20the%2017%20dialogue%20partners%20of%20the%20ASEAN%20Regional%20Forum%2C%20China%20has%20ensured%20that%20its%20economic%20ties%20in%20the%20region%20are%20both%20wide%20and%20deep.%20Together%2C%20they%20established%20the%20ASEAN-China%20Free%20Trade%20Area%2C%20which%20is%20currently%20being%20upgraded%20to%20cover%20more%20ground.%20The%20results%20are%20staggering%3A%20in%202023%20alone%2C%20China-ASEAN%20trade%20volume%20soared%20to%20%24911.7%20billion.%20For%20four%20consecutive%20years%2C%20China%20and%20ASEAN%20have%20been%20each%20other's%20largest%20trading%20partners%E2%80%94a%20testament%20to%20the%20strength%20and%20importance%20of%20this%20partnership.%20In%202024%2C%20China's%20trade%20surplus%20reached%20nearly%20%241%20trillion%2C%20and%20one-third%20of%20it%20came%20from%20trade%20with%20the%20US%20(as%20of%20last%20year%2C%20America%20maintains%20its%20position%20as%20the%20world's%20largest%20economy%2C%20with%20a%20GDP%20of%20just%20under%20%2429%20trillion.%20China%20follows%20as%20the%20second-largest%2C%20with%20a%20GDP%20of%20approximately%20%2418.5%20trillion).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20also%20been%20a%20driving%20force%20behind%20the%20Regional%20Comprehensive%20Economic%20Partnership%20(RCEP)%2C%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20free%20trade%20agreements%20in%20history.%20In%20effect%20since%20January%202022%2C%20the%20RCEP%20unites%2015%20Asia-Pacific%20countries%2C%20including%20Japan%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20Australia%2C%20New%20Zealand%20and%20the%2010%20ASEAN%20nations.%20Together%2C%20members%20of%20this%20powerhouse%20grouping%20account%20for%2030%25%20of%20the%20global%20GDP.%20Its%20aim%20is%20to%20eliminate%20tariffs%20on%2090%25%20of%20goods%20over%2020%20years%2C%20smoothening%20trade%20flows%2C%20and%20creating%20unprecedented%20market%20access.%20If%20Trump's%20tariffs%20are%20a%20hammer%2C%20then%20the%20RCEP%20is%20China's%20cushion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina's%20engagement%20with%20the%20Arab%20world%20has%20been%20equally%20calculated.%20By%20making%20the%20ties%20with%20the%20Gulf%20Cooperation%20Council%20(GCC)%20more%20robust%2C%20Beijing%20has%20emerged%20as%20the%20largest%20trading%20partner%20for%20many%20Arab%20nations.%20Trade%20between%20China%20and%20the%20Arab%20world%20skyrocketed%20from%20a%20modest%20%2436.7%20billion%20in%202004%20to%20a%20whopping%20%24431.4%20billion%20in%202022.%20Chinese%20investments%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20have%20also%20surged%2C%20targeting%20manufacturing%2C%20energy%20and%20infrastructure.%20This%20region%2C%20long%20dominated%20by%20the%20US%2C%20is%20increasingly%20looking%20eastward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%20afield%2C%20China%20has%20widened%20its%20economic%20footprint%20in%20Latin%20America%20and%20the%20Caribbean%20(LAC).%20Beijing%20has%20so%20far%20poured%20over%20%24138%20billion%20in%20loans%20into%20the%20region%2C%20providing%20a%20vital%20boost%20to%20developing%20economies.%20As%20per%20the%20latest%20data%20(2021)%2C%20China's%20trade%20with%20LAC%20stood%20at%20%24445%20billion.%20For%20many%20LAC%20nations%2C%20Beijing%20isn't%20just%20a%20trading%20partner%20but%20an%20indispensable%20ally%20in%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20For%20The%20Long%20Game%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECloser%20home%2C%20China's%20engagement%20with%20India%20shows%20its%20diplomatic%20pragmatism.%20The%20thaw%20in%20India-China%20relations%2C%20evidenced%20by%20Xi's%20meeting%20with%20Modi%20at%20the%20last%20BRICS%20summit%2C%20was%20followed%20by%20a%20de-escalation%20of%20military%20tensions%20and%20promises%20of%20expanded%20trade.%20And%2C%20in%20Australia%2C%20Premier%20Li%20Qiang's%20visit%20in%20mid-2024%20has%20revitalised%20Sino-Australian%20ties.%20That's%20two%20key%20Quad%20members%20China%20has%20managed%20to%20improve%20relations%20with%2C%20proof%20of%20its%20magnetic%20pull.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20highlights%20Beijing's%20readiness%20to%20counter%20external%20shocks.%20Trump%20can%20threaten%20tariffs%2C%20but%20China%20isn't%20going%20to%20stand%20still.%20It%20has%20positioned%20itself%20well%20to%20play%20the%20long%20game.%20What's%20more%2C%20even%20as%20analysts%20obsess%20over%20the%20confrontational%20aspects%20of%20US-China%20relations%2C%20signs%20of%20mutual%20recognition%20and%20goodwill%20persist.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20real%20question%20isn't%20whether%20Trump%20will%20stick%20to%20his%20campaign%20rhetoric%20or%20temper%20it%20in%20the%20face%20of%20reality%E2%80%94it's%20whether%20America%20is%20prepared%20for%20a%20trade%20war%20with%20a%20China%20that%20is%20far%20more%20fortified%20and%20resilient%20than%20it%20was%20four%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20perhaps%20it's%20time%20for%20the%20West%20to%20take%20a%20fresh%20view.%20Trump's%20stance%20on%20China%20is%20no%20longer%20a%20one-dimensional%20tale%20of%20bluster%20and%20bravado.%20His%20outreach%20to%20Xi%E2%80%94whether%20strategic%2C%20self-serving%2C%20or%20both%E2%80%94suggests%20he's%20playing%20a%20more%20complex%20game.%20If%20anything%2C%20the%20post-inauguration%20optics%20reveal%20that%20while%20Trump%20talks%20tough%2C%20he%20might%20just%20leave%20a%20door%20ajar%20for%20negotiations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Syed%20Zubair%20Ahmed%20is%20a%20London-based%20senior%20Indian%20journalist%20with%20three%20decades%20of%20experience%20with%20the%20Western%20media)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737536160000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-04%2Fxi-jinping-donald-trump-reuters_650x400_8149152009