EA%20soldier%2C%20who%20died%20as%20a%20German%20prisoner%20of%20war%20in%201941%2C%20was%20buried%20without%20his%20brain%2C%20a%20fact%20his%20family%20only%20discovered%20nearly%2080%20years%20later.%20Donnie%20MacRae%2C%20a%20private%20in%20the%20Seaforth%20Highlanders%2C%20was%20captured%20during%20the%20Battle%20of%20St%20Valery%20in%20France%20in%201940%20and%20died%20a%20year%20later%20in%20a%20prisoner-of-war%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMacRae%2C%2033%20at%20the%20time%2C%20died%20due%20to%20Guillain-Barre%20syndrome%2C%20a%20rare%20neurological%20condition.%20Following%20his%20death%2C%20an%20autopsy%20was%20performed%2C%20during%20which%20his%20brain%20and%20part%20of%20his%20spinal%20cord%20were%20removed%20for%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20samples%20were%20sent%20to%20the%20Kaiser%20Wilhelm%20Institute%20for%20Psychiatry%20in%20Munich%2C%20now%20the%20Max%20Planck%20Institute%20for%20Psychiatry%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc2kxl45kev0o%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBBC%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20his%20body%20was%20buried%20by%20the%20Germans%20and%20later%20reinterred%20by%20the%20Allies%20at%20a%20Commonwealth%20War%20Graves%20cemetery%20in%20Berlin%2C%20his%20family%20was%20unaware%20that%20his%20brain%20had%20been%20removed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20Professor%20Paul%20Weindling%20of%20Oxford%20Brookes%20University%20contacted%20MacRae's%20niece%2C%20Libby%20MacRae%2C%20revealing%20that%20160%20small%20slices%20of%20his%20brain%20and%20spinal%20cord%20had%20been%20preserved%20in%20the%20institute's%20archives.%20Prof%20Weindling%20leads%20a%20research%20project%20to%20identify%20victims%20whose%20brain%20samples%20were%20taken%20during%20World%20War%20II%20and%20to%20ensure%20their%20proper%20commemoration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20overlooked%20group%20is%20certainly%20prisoners%20of%20war%20whose%20b