2025%3A%20What%20Is%20The%20Economic%20Survey%2C%20When%20Is%20It%20Presented%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Economic%20Survey%202024-25%2C%20scheduled%20for%20release%20on%20January%2031%2C%20will%20provide%20a%20detailed%20analysis%20of%20India's%20economic%20performance%20over%20the%20past%20financial%20year.%20Released%20a%20day%20before%20the%20Union%20Budget%202025%2C%20the%20report%20will%20highlight%20key%20trends%20across%20sectors%20like%20agriculture%2C%20industry%20and%20services%20while%20offering%20policy%20recommendations%20to%20address%20challenges%20and%20promote%20growth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Budget%20session%20in%20Parliament%20will%20start%20on%20January%2031%20and%20will%20conclude%20on%20April%204.%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20will%20present%20her%20eighth%20straight%20Budget%20on%20February%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20Economic%20Survey%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Economic%20Survey%20is%20a%20critical%20document%20released%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Finance%20ahead%20of%20the%20Budget.%20It%20provides%20a%20detailed%20analysis%20of%20economic%20trends%20in%20the%20country%20and%20aids%20in%20understanding%20how%20resources%20are%20mobilised%20and%20allocated%20in%20the%20Budget.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIt%20is%20prepared%20by%20the%20Economic%20Division%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Economic%20Affairs%20under%20the%20Chief%20Economic%20Advisor%20(CEA)%20and%20is%20divided%20into%20two%20parts.%20Part%20A%20reviews%20the%20country's%20economic%20performance%2C%20focusing%20on%20fiscal%20trends%20and%20macroeconomic%20indicators%2C%20while%20Part%20B%20explores%20socio-economic%20issues%20like%20education%2C%20poverty%2C%20and%20climate%20change%2C%20along%20with%20projections%20for%20GDP%20growth%2C%20inflation%20and%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Economic%20Survey%20evaluates%20key%20economic%20indicators%20such%20as%20agricultural%20and%20industrial%20production%2C%20infrastructure%2C%20employment%2C%20money%20supply%2C%20prices%2C%20imports%2C%20exports%20and%20foreign%20exchange%20reserves.%20It%20facilitates%20a%20comprehensive%20understanding%20of%20factors%20influencing%20the%20economy%20and%20their%20impact%20on%20the%20government's%20fiscal%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20is%20the%20Economic%20Survey%20presented%20before%20the%20Budget%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Economic%20Survey%20is%20released%20before%20the%20Budget%20to%20give%20a%20clear%20picture%20of%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhile%20the%20Budget%20outlines%20the%20government's%20receipts%20and%20expenditures%2C%20it%20also%20serves%20as%20a%20significant%20policy%20document.%20The%20Economic%20Survey%20complements%20this%20by%20offering%20an%20in-depth%20view%20of%20how%20these%20fiscal%20measures%20are%20shaped%20by%20the%20broader%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Ministry%20of%20Finance%20releases%20a%20Functional%20Classification%20of%20the%20Budget%2C%20analysing%20expenditures%20in%20terms%20of%20economic%20priorities%20like%20capital%20formation%20and%20sectoral%20transfers%20through%20grants%20and%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Survey%20helps%20policymakers%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESet%20realistic%20revenue%20and%20expenditure%20targets%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAddress%20challenges%20like%20unemployment%20and%20inflation%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EPrioritise%20sectors%20needing%20immediate%20focus%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%20dir%3D%5C%2